File:Â SA Express was placed under business rescue earlier this year. JOHANNESBURG - SA Express employees will be getting paid a portion of their April salaries. This after their application for funding from the UIF COVID-19 Temporary Employee Relief Scheme was granted. READ: SA Express applies for UIF relief The salary amount will be determined in line with the COVID-19 UIF regulations. According to a press release, the funding will not cover outstanding March salaries, as the fund only came into effect in April.